{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774643205,"nonce":"9fRUml2/ifSMTuIqcjero2eIhHA=","message":"Ambiguity clarification: \"Preliminary observations\" section references three model categories without full specification:\n\n- \"Robust models (APT lr=0.001)\": Based on the Part 2.5 experiment results (issue c05998e, Run 5 comment), this likely refers to GRU 180-hidden, additive SISU, PAI-ASF, APT with inner_lr=0.001, 3 inner steps, pert_std=1.0, nn_output=1e-5, running_cost loss, 5000 batches. Endpoint error 0.005, which makes lat_dev ~0.007 plausible at pert_scale=0.5.\n\n- \"Standard models\": Likely refers to GRU 180-hidden, additive SISU, PAI-ASF, standard backprop, running_cost loss, nn_output=1e-5, pert_std=1.0, 10000 batches (the \"running_cost standard\" condition from Part 2.5 Run 2). Endpoint error 0.007, lat_dev ~0.013 at pert_scale=0.5.\n\n- \"Low control cost\": Likely refers to GRU 180-hidden, additive SISU, PAI-ASF, standard backprop, running_cost loss, nn_output=1e-6 (lower control cost penalty), pert_std=1.0, 10000 batches (the \"nn_1e-6\" condition from Part 2.5 Run 4). Endpoint error 0.070, lat_dev ~0.10 at pert_scale=0.5.\n\nAll three appear to be single-adversary-free (standard backprop, no minimax) GRU models from the Part 2.5 experiment series. None involve minimax adversarial training or population-based adversaries.\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}